<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN ONOFRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Mexican man running across Interstate 5 near the San Onofre Nuclear Power 
Plant was struck by four vehicles and killed early Sunday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
He was identified as Primitivo Cuevas, 33, who was seen about 12:30 a.m. 
running across the interstate just south of the U. S. Border Patrol checkpoint. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego County coroner's office said Cuevas was struck by four vehicles 
and died at the scene of multiple injuries. 
</P>
<P>
A Border Patrol spokesman said Sunday afternoon that officials had not yet 
determined whether Cuevas was an undocumented worker attempting to slip through 
the checkpoint. 
</P>
</TEXT>
