<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Producer to Cut Agents' Cuts: Producer Cameron Mackintosh, who made Broadway 
history by charging $100 for top seats to next season's "Miss Saigon," is 
causing more woes among New York theater ticket agents. Mackintosh, who also 
produced "Les Miserables" and "Phantom of the Opera," has told the agents, who 
sell millions of dollars of tickets in advance block ticket sales, that 
"Saigon" will not pay the flat 10% commission that has long been standard 
industry practice. His new flexible commission scale will range from 5% for the 
best seats to 10% on the hardest-to-unload. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
