<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beach Boys Movie Sued: Irving Music Co. has sued a film production company, 
accusing them of lying to win permission to use Beach Boys songs in an ABC 
television movie based on an unauthorized biography of the surf-music group. 
The Los Angeles Superior Court suit alleges Leonard Hill Productions told 
Irving agents that they wanted to use the songs for a "teen-age coming-of-age 
story" or in a film about "vacationing kids who liked Beach Boys music." The 
ABC film, "The Story of the Beach Boys: Summer Dreams" aired Sunday. GREG 
BRAXTON 
</P>
