<P>
"THE CONDUCTOR"(France-Belgium, 1989; Director: Marion Hansel. Century Plaza 2, 
7 p.m.) Exquisitely wrought meditation on the nature of identity, involving 
guilt and responsibility, with a classical music background. The acting is 
wonderful: including Malcolm McDowell's best performance in years. As in many 
international co-productions, though, the mix of nationalities may unsettle 
some audiences. (Kevin Thomas). 
