<P>
"THE HELLSTROM CHRONICLE"(U.S., 1971; D: Walon Green. Century Plaza 3, 7 p.m.). 
The narrative device is slightly absurd, but, back in 1971, this film's 
microphotography of insects at work and war blew audience's minds. It still 
should. Part of the David Wolper Tribute. (Michael Wilmington) 
</P>
<P>
"KINDERGARTEN"(USSR: 1985; D: Yevgeny Yevtushenko. Fairfax, 9:15 p.m.) First 
film by the famed Russian poet: uneven, flamboyant, deeply personal, 
semi-autobiographical.(Michael Wilmington) 
</P>
