<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BENN BEATS DEWITT FOR WBO MIDDLEWEIGHT TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nigel Benn won the World Boxing Organization middleweight title by stopping 
defending champion Doug DeWitt in the eighth round of a scheduled 12-round bout 
Sunday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Referee Randy Newman, following WBO rules, halted the bout when Benn floored 
DeWitt three times in the eighth. Benn's final knockdown came from a left 
uppercut 44 seconds into the round. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Benn dropped DeWitt with a right uppercut and with a left hook-right 
combination. 
</P>
<P>
Benn, 26, based in London, is 26-1 with 24 knockouts. DeWitt, 28, and fighting 
out of Yonkers, N.Y., is 32-7-4 with 19 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
