<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The following is a summary of Southern California-related business litigation 
developments during the week of April 23: 
</P>
<P>
Pathe Communications Suit: Pathe Communications Corp. sued businessman Giovanni 
DiStefano in Los Angeles Superior Court, claiming he owes $1.7 million for an 
unpaid loan, rent and services, and contractual damages for failing to purchase 
Pathe shares as he allegedly promised. The suit follows DiStefano's libel suit 
filed April 20, in which he seeks $281 million plus punitive damages because 
Pathe took out newspaper ads saying he had never been a company director or 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
DiStefano says he was a senior vice president "virtually in charge of sales and 
acquisitions" from November, 1989, until early this year. (Filed April 23, 
1990. Case No. C759178) 
</P>
</TEXT>
