<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The following is a summary of Southern California-related business litigation 
developments during the week of April 23: 
</P>
<P>
Fox Sued Over Manson Interview: Fox Broadcasting Co. was sued in Los Angeles 
Superior Court by Nikolas Schrenk, who claims Fox failed to get approval before 
using parts of his 1988 interview with convicted killer Charles Manson. 
</P>
<P>
The breach-of-contract suit alleges that Fox agreed Schrenk would approve its 
use of any footage from the Manson interview, broadcast in mid-1989 on "A 
Current Affair." Schrenk seeks unstated damages for revenue allegedly lost from 
expected sales of videotapes and other TV broadcasts of the interview. (Filed 
April 23, 1990. Case No. C759166) 
</P>
</TEXT>
