<P>
RAIL VICTIM FOUND ALONG TRACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who apparently fell off a train in the Canyon Country area was run over 
and killed by a rail car, Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies said today. 
</P>
<P>
The body of the unidentified man, believed to be in his 20s, was discovered 
about 8 p.m. Sunday next to tracks near the Lang railroad station at Shadow 
Pines Boulevard and the Antelope Valley Freeway, deputies said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
