<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE; 
</P>
<P>
MILLION SIGN VAN DE KAMP PROP. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Democrat gubernatorial candidate John K. Van de Kamp said today that he has 1 
million signatures to qualify a ballot measure that would limit state 
politicians to 12 years in office. 
</P>
<P>
The number is far in excess of the 595,000 needed to qualify the measure for 
the November ballot. 
</P>
<P>
"Something seems to happen to people who stay too long in power," Van de Kamp 
said. "They start to think the position is theirs by right, rather than by 
grant from the people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
